{
  "stem": "13817.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then when the ones we had before came back, they were even worse than the ones we got in replacement, because [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it happened on their shift that the guy-- when the guy escaped.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's the only escape I know of which was successful.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then in the morning, we would march again.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when we-- we were marching-- for instance, you can think of the German mentality at that time when the war was practically lost.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Russians were right there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The-- the Germans-- the Germans-- in one little town, a woman came out with a-- like a drawer full of glowing ash from the oven, from the stove, and threw that over us and called us dirty Jews.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that was still the mentality of Hitler's time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was in January of '45, and already everything was more or less lost.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then we went to Gleiwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in Gleiwitz, again we-- we were put on open coal wagons, about 100, 150 people into a coal wagon.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We got about three slices of bread, and then off we went again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We didn't know where we were going again there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There again, we didn't know where we were headed to.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there were-- like I said, the coal wagons were open and it started snowing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And everybody was just cold, freezing in there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And to-- to get any water, we would pick the snow from each other's back and use this as-- as liquid so we would have something to drink or liquid in our-- in our system.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
